     1	# x-agent
     2	
     3	Every time your coding agent runs a lint or test cycle, it burns thousands of tokens on compilation progress and passing test names. x-agent cuts 90-97% of that noise — your agent gets structured pass/fail, you keep your context window for actual code.
     4	
     5	## Why?
     6	
     7	Standard build tools produce walls of text. Agents waste context window parsing noise. x-agent scripts give:
     8	
     9	- **Structured output** — `Step: lint`, `Result: PASS`, `Overall: FAIL`
    10	- **Truncated diagnostics** — only the first N lines of errors/warnings (configurable)
    11	- **Full logs on disk** — temp dir path printed so the agent can read more if needed
    12	- **Consistent interface** — same env knobs and output format across all runners
    13	
    14	## Available Agents
    15	
    16	| Agent | Toolchain | Steps |
    17	|-------|-----------|-------|
    18	| `ansible-agent` | Ansible | lint (ansible-lint), syntax (ansible-playbook --syntax-check) |
    19	| `bash-agent` | Bash/Shell | syntax (bash -n), lint (shellcheck) |
    20	| `cargo-agent` | Rust | fmt, check, clippy, test (nextest) |
